rtarians]]\n[[Category:New York (state) Republicans]]\n[[Category:People from Smithtown, New York]]\n[[Category:Private equity and venture capital investors]]\n[[Category:Republican Party state governors of the United States]]\n[[Category:United States Assistant Attorneys General for the Criminal Division]]\n[[Category:United States Attorneys for the District of Massachusetts]]\n[[Category:Wilmer Cutler Pickering Hale and Dorr partners]]\n", "name_user": "Chris the speller", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200e2020 presidential campaign:replaced: President \u2192 president", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bill_Weld"}
{"title_page": "A.P. Bio", "text_new": "{{About|the 2018 comedy series|the course offered by the College Board|AP Biology}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name = A.P. Bio\n| image = File:AP Bio Logo.png\n| caption =\n| genre = [[Television comedy|Comedy]]\n| creator = [[Mike O'Brien (actor)|Mike O'Brien]]\n| director =\n| starring = {{Plainlist|\n*[[Glenn Howerton]]\n*Lyric Lewis\n*Mary Sohn\n*Jean Villepique\n*[[Tom Bennett (actor)|Tom Bennett]]\n*[[Patton Oswalt]]\n*[[Paula Pell]]\n}}\n| composer = [[Jeff Cardoni]]\n| opentheme = \"Listen to My Heart\" by [[Ramones]]\n| country = United States\n| language = English\n| num_seasons = 2\n| num_episodes = 26\n| list_episodes = \n| executive_producer = {{Plainlist|\n*Mike O'Brien\n*[[Seth Meyers]]\n*[[Lorne Michaels]]\n*Andrew Singer\n*Michael Shoemaker\n}}\n| producer = {{Plainlist|\n*Hilary Marx\n*Katy Jenson\n*Shelly Gossman\n*Glenn Howerton\n*Barbara Stoll\n}}\n| editor = {{Plainlist|\n*Adam Lichtenstein\n*Dane McMaster\n}}\n| location =\n| cinematography = Blake McClure\n| camera = [[Single-camera setup|Single-camera]]\n| runtime = 22 minutes\n| company = {{Plainlist|\n*[[Broadway Video]]\n*Sethmaker Shoemeyers Productions\n*Human Rabbit (season 2)\n*[[Universal Television]]\n}}\n| distributor = [[NBCUniversal Television Distribution]]\n| network = [[NBC]] (seasons 1\u20132) <!--[[Peacock (streaming service)|Peacock]]-->\n| picture_format = [[1080i]] ([[High-definition television|HDTV]])\n| audio_format =\n| first_aired = {{Start date|2018|2|1}}\n| last_aired = {{End date|present}}\n| related =\n| website =\n}}\n\n'''''A.P. Bio''''' is an American [[Television comedy|comedy]] television series created by [[Mike O'Brien (actor)|Mike O'Brien]] for [[NBC]]. The series premiered on February 1, 2018 for a special preview and made its official debut on March 1, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/12/ap-bio-february-preview-date-this-is-us-midseason-return-premiere-1202227148/|title=NBC's 'A.P. Bio' Gets February Preview Date, 'This Is Us' Midseason Return Moved Back A Week|last=Petski|first=Denise|work=Deadline Hollywood|date=December 14, 2017|accessdate=December 14, 2017}}</ref> NBC released the first three episodes on NBCUniversal streaming platforms after the February 1 broadcast premiere for early viewing.\n\nIn May 2018, the series was renewed for a second season that premiered on March 7, 2019. In May 2019, the series was cancelled after two seasons. The following month, [[Peacock (streaming service)|Peacock]] picked up the series for a third season.\n\n==Plot==\nWhen disgraced [[Harvard]] [[philosophy]] professor Jack Carson Griffin ([[Glenn Howerton]]) loses out on his dream job to his rival Miles Leonard ([[Tom Bennett (actor)|Tom Bennett]]), he is forced to return to [[Toledo, Ohio]] and work as an [[AP Biology|advanced placement biology]] teacher at the fictional Whitlock High School. Jack makes it clear to his class that he will not be teaching any biology. Realising he has a room full of honor-roll students at his disposal, Jack decides to use them for his own benefit: getting revenge on Miles. Eager to prove that he is still king of the castle, Principal Durbin ([[Patton Oswalt]]) struggles to keep Griffin under control. In its second season, Jack uses his students to find out how the people of Toledo find happiness in their daily routine, so as to mine information for what he believes will be a best-selling book.\n\n==Cast==\n===Main cast===\n*[[Glenn Howerton]] as Dr. Jack Carson Griffin, a disgraced Harvard philosophy scholar and current Advanced Placement Biology teacher at Whitlock High School.\n*Lyric Lewis as Stef Duncan, a history teacher at Whitlock High School.\n*Mary Sohn as Mary Wagner, an art teacher at Whitlock High School.\n*Jean Villepique as Michelle Jones, a home economics teacher at Whitlock High School.\n*[[Tom Bennett (actor)|Tom Bennett]] as Miles Leonard, a scholar who is Jack's rival and nemesis. (<small>Season 1</small>)\n*[[Paula Pell]] as Helen Henry Demarcus, Principal Durbin's secretary (<small>Season 2, Recurring Season 1</small>)\n*[[Patton Oswalt]] as Principal Ralph Durbin, the principal of Whitlock High School.\n\n===Recurring===\n*Jacob McCarthy as Devin (<small>Season 1</small>)\n*[[Aparna Brielle]] as Sarika Sarkar\n*Nick Peine as Marcus Kasperak\n*[[Allisyn Ashley Arm]] as Heather\n*Eddie Leavy as Anthony Lewis\n*Charlie McCrackin as Coach Dick Novak\n*Jacob Houston as Victor Kozlowski\n*[[Tucker Albrizzi]] as Colin McConnell (<small>Season 1</small>)\n*[[Spence Moore II]] as Dan Decker\n*Sari Arambulo as Grace\n*[[Elizabeth Alderfer]] as Lynette (<small>Season 2</small>)\n*Miguel Chavez as Eduardo\n*Marisa Baram as Marissa\n\n===Guest stars===\n*[[Collette Wolfe]] as Meredith\n*[[Nikki Glaser]] as Chloe from Baltimore\n*[[Niecy Nash]] as Kim Burke\n*[[Taran Killam]] as Mr. Vining\n*[[Mark Proksch]] as Philip\n*[[Michael Gross (actor)|Michael Gross]] as Brandon\n*[[Christopher Lloyd]] as Melvin\n*[[Erinn Hayes]] as Trish\n*[[Tim Heidecker]] as Greg\n*[[Brooks Wheelan]] as Seth\n\n==Episodes==\n{{Series overview\n| color1    = #CCC1A8\n| link1     = #Season 1 (2018)\n| episodes1 = 13\n| start1    = {{Start date|2018|2|1}}\n| end1      = {{End date|2018|5|3}}\n| network1 = [[NBC]]\n\n| color2    = #C1CCA8\n| link2     = #Season 2 (2019)\n| episodes2 = 13\n| start2    = {{Start date|2019|3|7}}\n| end2      = {{End date|2019|6|13}}\n| network 2 = NBC\n<!--\n| color2    = \n| link2     = #Season 3 (2020)\n| episodes2 = 13\n| start2    = \n| end2      = \n| network 2 = NBCUniversal -->\n}}\n\n===Season 1 (2018)===\n{{Episode table|background=#CCC1A8|overall=|season=|title=|director=|writer=|airdate=|viewers=|country=U.S.|prodcode=|episodes=\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 1\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 1\n |Title           = Catfish\n |DirectedBy      = Oz Rodriguez\n |WrittenBy       = [[Mike O'Brien (actor)|Mike O'Brien]]\n |OriginalAirDate ={{Start date|2018|2|1}}\n |ProdCode        