 a second season, which premiered on March 7, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/tv/news/ap-bio-renewed-nbc-abbys-i-feel-bad-1202801882/|title='AP Bio' Renewed for Season 2 at NBC, Comedies 'Abby's,' 'I Feel Bad' Ordered to Series|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|last=Otterson|first=Joe|date=May 8, 2018|access-date=May 15, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/12/nbc-premiere-dates-midseaswon-2019-the-voice-world-of-dance-a-p-bio-good-girls-enemy-within-the-village-1202522095/|title=NBC Sets Premiere Dates For New Dramas \u2018Enemy Within\u2019 & \u2018The Village\u2019, Return For \u2018Good Girls\u2019, \u2018The Voice\u2019, \u2018World Of Dance\u2019|last1=Andreeva|first1=Nellie|last2=Pedersen|first2=Erik|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=December 18, 2018|language=en|date=December 18, 2018}}</ref> On May 24, 2019, NBC cancelled the show after two seasons.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Iannucci|first1=Rebecca|title=A.P. Bio Cancelled at NBC|url=https://tvline.com/2019/05/24/ap-bio-cancelled-season-3-nbc/|website=TVLine|accessdate=May 25, 2019|language=en|date=May 24, 2019}}</ref> In July 2019, NBC reversed this decision and renewed the series for a third season, which is set to premiere on NBCUniversal's upcoming streaming service, [[Peacock (streaming service)|Peacock]].<ref>{{citeweb|last1=Goldberg|first1=Lesley|title=A.P. Bio Revived for Season 3 on NBCUniversal's Streaming Service (Exclusive)|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/ap-bio-revived-season-3-nbcuniversals-streaming-service-1224478|website=The Hollywood Reporter|accessdate=July 17, 2019|language=en|date=July 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Casting===\nIn February 2017, it was announced that Mary Sohn and Lyric Lewis had joined the pilot's main cast.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/02/gillian-vigman-cast-the-cw-life-sentence-mary-sohn-nbc-seth-meyers-1201958048/|title=Gillian Vigman Cast In The CW's 'Life Sentence' Pilot; Mary Sohn in NBC's Seth Meyers Comedy|last=Petski|first=Denise|work=Deadline Hollywood|date=February 24, 2017|accessdate=February 24, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/02/for-god-and-country-noah-mills-cast-lyric-lewis-seth-meyers-nbc-1202029014/|title=Noah Mills Enlists In 'For God And Country'; Lyric Lewis Joins NBC's Seth Meyers Pilot|last=Hipes|first=Patrick|work=Deadline Hollywood|date=February 28, 2017|accessdate=February 28, 2017}}</ref> In March 2017, it was reported that [[Aparna Brielle]], [[Glenn Howerton]], [[Patton Oswalt]], Nick Peine and Jacob McCarthy had joined the cast in their main roles.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/03/redliners-greg-germann-nbc-drama-pilot-aparna-brielle-seth-meyers-comedy-1202038060/|title='Redliners': Greg Germann Joins NBC Drama Pilot; Aparna Brielle In Seth Meyers Comedy|last=Petski|first=Denise|work=Deadline Hollywood|date=March 7, 2017|accessdate=March 7, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/03/glenn-howerton-patton-oswalt-star-nbc-mike-obrien-seth-meyers-pilot-1202039486/|title=Glenn Howerton & Patton Oswalt To Star In NBC's Mike O'Brien/Seth Meyers Pilot|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|work=Deadline Hollywood|date=March 8, 2017|accessdate=March 8, 2017|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/03/nick-peine-seth-meyer-the-get-alex-fitzalan-1202040717/|title=NBC's Seth Meyers Comedy Pilot Casts Nick Peine; CBS' 'The Get' Adds Alex Fitzalan|last=Petski|first=Denise|work=Deadline Hollywood|date=March 10, 2017|accessdate=March 10, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/03/christopher-gorham-the-cw-insatiable-nbcs-seth-meyers-comedy-jacob-mccarthy-1202043069/|title=Christopher Gorham Joins the CW's 'Insatiable'; NBC's Seth Meyers Comedy Adds Jacob McCarthy|last=Petski|first=Denise|work=Deadline Hollywood|date=March 14, 2017|accessdate=March 14, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/03/redliners-greg-germann-nbc-drama-pilot-aparna-brielle-seth-meyers-comedy-1202038060/|title='Redliners': Greg Germann Joins NBC Drama Pilot; Aparna Brielle In Seth Meyers Comedy|last=Petski|first=Denise|work=Deadline Hollywood|date=March 7, 2017|accessdate=March 7, 2017}}</ref> On June 12, 2017, it was announced that [[Tom Bennett (actor)|Tom Bennett]] had joined the series regular.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/ap-bio-promotes-tom-bennett-series-regular-1012677|title=\nNBC's 'A.P. Bio' Promotes 'Mascots' Star to Series Regular (Exclusive)|last=Stanhope|first=Kate|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=June 12, 2017|accessdate=January 26, 2018}}</ref> On August 1, 2017, it was announced that Jean Villepique had joined the series regular.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/08/a-p-bio-jean-villepique-cast-regular-nbc-comedy-seth-meyers-1202140158/|title='A.P. Bio': Jean Villepique Cast As Regular In NBC Comedy|last=Petski|first=Denise|work=Deadline Hollywood|date=August 1, 2017|accessdate=January 26, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Critical response===\nThe first season holds a score of 65% with an average rating of 6.34/10 on the [[review aggregation]] website [[Rotten Tomatoes]], based on 31 reviews. The site's critical consensus states: \"''A.P. Bio'' has some genuine laughs, but audiences have already seen plenty of authority figures behaving badly -- and have a right to expect more from this promising premise and talented cast.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/a_p_bio/s01/|title= A.P. BIO: SEASON 1 (2018)|website= [[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate= January 27, 2019}}</ref> [[Metacritic]], which uses a weighted average, assigned the series a score of 59 out of 100 based on 16 critics.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/tv/ap-bio|title=A.P. Bio: Season 1|website=[[Metacritic]]|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]|accessdate=February 9, 2019}}</ref>\n\nWriting in ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'', Daniel Fienberg commented that ''A.P. Bio'' had a good cast and \"the only thing holding it back is the small quibble that it's not actually all that funny.\"<ref>{{cite news|last1=Fienberg|first1=Daniel|title='AP Bio': TV Review|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/ap-bio-review-1080713|accessdate=February 8, 2018|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=February 1, 2018}}</ref> Margaret Lyons of the ''[[New York Times]]'' called ''A.P. Bio'' \"an abrasive sitcom that isn't merely unfunny, it's also deeply unpleasant.\"<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lyons|first1=Margaret|title=Review: 'A.P. Bio' Is Not Advanced in Timing or Taste|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/01/31/arts/television/ap-bio-review.html|accessdate=February 8, 2018|work=[[New York Times]]|date=January 31, 2018}}</ref> Jen Chaney of [[Vulture (website)|Vulture]] said the series had bright spots but was \"conceptually played-out\" overall.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Chaney|first1=Jen|title=A.P. Bio Isn't Exactly Advanced Placement TV|url=http://www.vulture.com/2018/01/ap-bio-nbc-review.html|accessdate=February 8, 2018|work=Vulture|date=January 31, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Ratings===\n====Overall====\n{{Television season ratings\n| hide_18_49_rating = y\n\n| link1             = #Season 1 (2018)\n| timeslot1         = Thursday 8:30&nbsp;pm\n| timeslot_length1  = 2\n| episodes1         = 13\n| start1            = {{Start date|2018|2|1}}\n| startrating1      = 3.12<ref name=\"1.01\"/>\n| end1              = {{End date|2018|5|3}}\n| endrating1        = 2.03<ref name=\"1.13\"/>\n| season1           = 2017\u201318\n| rank1             = 134\n| viewers1          = 3.54<ref name=\"entertainment2018\">{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2018/05/2017-2018-tv-series-ratings-rankings-full-list-of-shows-1202395851/|title=2017-18 TV Series Ratings Rankings: NFL Football, 'Big Bang' Top Charts|work=Deadline Hollywood|last1=de Moraes|first1=Lisa|last2=Hipes|first2=Patrick|date=May 22, 2018|accessdate=March 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\n| link2             = #Season 2 (2019)\n| episodes2         = 13\n| start2       